communityconfiguration-mentorship-info-t:
This message describes the roles of mentors within the community. It explains that newcomers are automatically assigned to mentors. Mentors can choose to claim mentees manually. The recommended number of mentors is one mentor for each group of 500 new accounts, with a minimum of 3 mentors. Additionally, mentees can receive encouraging messages from established editors, which can improve new editor retention. The Personalized praise module highlights praiseworthy new editors to their mentor, fostering a sense of engagement and involvement in the community.

* "Mentor dashboard" is {{msg-mw|Growthexperiments-mentor-dashboard-title}}
* "Automatically assigned mentors" is {{msg-mw|Growthexperiments-manage-mentors-auto-assigned}}
* "Manually assigned mentors" is {{msg-mw|Growthexperiments-manage-mentors-manually-assigned}}
* "Personalized praise" is {{msg-mw|Growthexperiments-edit-config-personalized-praise}}

